CIC/References/Context_Objects.html.body:
Context information
Context indicates various states information of a client. Context information is included in a context object which is sent with an Event message of the CIC APIs. Context should contain states information at the time when user's speech input is initiated. Available context objects are as follows.

AudioPlayer.PlaybackState
Device.DeviceState
Clova.FreetalkState
Clova.Location
Clova.SavedPlace
Speaker.VolumeState

AudioPlayer.PlaybackState 
PlaybackState is a message format containing information of the media which is currently being played or was lastly played. This information may be delivered using a custom extension message that provides music service in the future.
Message format
{
  "header": {
    "namespace": "AudioPlayer",
    "name": "PlaybackState"
  },
  "payload": {
    "offsetInMilliseconds": {{number}},
    "totalInMilliseconds": {{number}},
    "playerActivity": {{string}},
    "stream": {{AudioStreamObject}}
  }
}

Payload field



Field name
Type
Field description
Required




offsetInMilliseconds
number
The last playback point (offset) of the media recently played. The unit is a millisecond. This field can be left empty when playerActivity is "IDLE".
No


playerActivity
string
Indicates the state of the player. Available values are: "IDLE": Player is in an idle state"PLAYING": Player is in a playing state"PAUSED": Player is in a paused state"STOPPED": Player is in a stopped state
Yes


stream
AudioStreamObject
The object storing details of the currently playing media. This field can be left empty when playerActivity is "IDLE". Enter the media information (stream object) which was delivered in AudioPlayer.Play or AudioPlayer.StreamDelivered Directive message.
No


totalInMilliseconds
number
The total length of the media recently played. The unit is a millisecond. This field can be left empty when playerActivity is "IDLE".
No



Message example
Example 1: When playback is stopped
// Case 1: When playback is stopped
{
  "header": {
    "namespace": "AudioPlayer",
    "name": "PlaybackState"
  },
  "payload": {
    "offsetInMilliseconds": 1,
    "totalInMilliseconds": 100,
    "playerActivity": "STOPPED",
    "stream": {
      "beginAtInMilliseconds": 0,
      "progressReport": {
        "progressReportDelayInMilliseconds": null,
        "progressReportIntervalInMilliseconds": null,
        "progressReportPositionInMilliseconds": 60000
      },
      "token": "TR-NM-17740107",
      "url": "clova:TR-NM-17740107"
    }
  }
}

Example 2: When the player is in an inactive state
{
  "header": {
    "namespace": "AudioPlayer",
    "name": "PlaybackState"
  },
  "payload": {
    "playerActivity": "IDLE"
  }
}

See also

AudioPlayer.Play
AudioPlayer.StreamDeliver
AudioPlayer.StreamRequested

Device.DeviceState 
DeviceState is a message format used to send state information of a client device such as the current local time of a device.
Message format
{
  "header": {
    "namespace": "Device",
    "name": "DeviceState"
  },
  "payload": {
    "localTime": {{string}}
  }
}

Payload field



Field name
Type
Field description
Required




localTime
string
The current time set in the client device (ISO 8601 format)
Yes



Message example
{
  "header": {
    "namespace": "Device",
    "name": "DeviceState"
  },
  "payload": {
    "localTime": "2017-04-06T13:34:15.074361+08:28"
  }
}

See also

SpeechRecognizer.Recognize

Clova.FreetalkState 
FreetalkState is a message format that indicates the current state of the Clova Freetalk service in your client.
Message format
{
  "header": {
      "namespace": "Clova",
      "name": "FreetalkState"
  },
  "payload": {
      "foreground": {{boolean}},
      "reprompt": {{boolean}}
  }
}

Payload field



Field name
Type
Field description
Required




foreground
boolean
Whether the Freetalk mode is activated or not true: Activated.false: Inactivated.
Yes


reprompt
boolean
Whether re-prompted the user to input a response or not. This value verifies whether your client requested input from the user one more time after it did not receive user input for a specified time. true: The user was re-prompted to input a response; the Freetalk mode is finished.false: The user was not re-prompted to input a response; still waiting for a response.
Yes



Remarks
The Freetalk mode is available only in English at the moment. If the value of foreground field is true, the lang field of the Recognize Event message of SpeechRecognizer should be "en".
Message example
{
  "header": {
      "namespace": "Clova",
      "name": "FreetalkState"
  },
  "payload": {
      "foreground": flase,
      "reprompt": true
  }
}

See also

SpeechRecognizer.Recognize

Clova.Location 
This message format is used to send the current location of your client. Your client may obtain the location information from GPS, base stations, or network devices and send the information to CIC.
Message format
{
  "header": {
    "namespace": "Clova",
    "name": "Location"
  },
  "payload": {
    "latitude": {{string}},
    "longitude": {{string}},
    "refreshedAt": {{string}}
  }
}

Payload field



Field name
Type
Field description
Required




latitude
string
Latitude
Yes


longitude
string
Longitude
Yes


refreshedAt
string
The time when the location was last checked (UTC, ISO 8601 format)
Yes



Message example
{
  "header": {
    "namespace": "Clova",
    "name": "Location"
  },
  "payload": {
    "latitude": "37.3594915",
    "longitude": "127.1032242",
    "refreshedAt": "2017-04-06T13:34:15.074361+08:28"
  }
}

See also

SpeechRecognizer.Recognize

Clova.SavedPlace 
This message format is used to send the location information previously saved in your client.
Message format
{
  "header": {
    "namespace": "Clova",
    "name": "SavedPlace"
  },
  "payload": {
    "places": [
      {
        "latitude": {{string}},
        "longitude": {{string}},
        "refreshedAt": {{string}}
        "name": {{string}}
      }
    ]
  }
}

Payload field



Field name
Type
Field description
Required




places[]
object array
The object array containing the previously saved location information
Yes


places[].latitude
string
Latitude
Yes


places[].longitude
string
Longitude
Yes


places[].name
string
The name of the location saved. Available values are: 회사집
Yes


places[].refreshedAt
string
The time when the location was saved (UTC, ISO 8601 format)
Yes



Message example
{
  "header": {
    "namespace": "Clova",
    "name": "SavedPlace"
  },
  "payload": {
    "places": [
      {
        "latitude": "37.3594915",
        "longitude": "127.1032242",
        "refreshedAt": "2017-04-06T13:34:15.074361+08:28"
        "name": "집"
      },
      {
        "latitude": "36.3542315",
        "longitude": "125.1345242",
        "refreshedAt": "2017-03-12T10:21:33.089723+08:28"
        "name": "회사"
      }
    ]
  }
}

See also

SpeechRecognizer.Recognize

Speaker.VolumeState 
This message format contains the information of the client speaker at the time user's speech input is initiated, such as the volume size or whether the speaker is muted or not.
Message format
{
  "header": {
      "namespace": "Speaker",
      "name": "VolumeState"
  },
  "payload": {
      "volume": {{number}},
      "muted": {{boolean}}
  }
}

Payload field



Field name
Type
Field description
Required




muted
boolean
Whether the speaker is muted or not
Yes


volume
number
The current volume size of the speaker (0-10)
Yes



Message example
{
  "header": {
      "namespace": "Speaker",
      "name": "VolumeState"
  },
  "payload": {
      "volume": 8,
      "muted": false
  }
}

See also

SpeechRecognizer.Recognize

CIC/References/ContentTemplates/CardList.body:
CardList Template
This template lets your client display data on a screen using a card list format. CardList has several card types as follows. Each card type consists of different card objects.



Card type
Type description
Fields of card object




Type1
Displays image, title, and description of the content.
description, imageUrl, referenceText, referenceUrl, title


Type2
Displays image, title, description, and link of the content.
description, imageUrl, linkUrl, referenceText, referenceUrl, title


Type3
Displays video content.
description, imageUrl, referenceText, referenceUrl, title, videoUrl


Type4
Displays news content.
description, press, pressIconUrl, publishDate, title




Note!
See Screen UI example for the available display formats of each type.


Template field



Field name
Type
Field description
Required




cardList[]
object array
The object array that displays the card list
Yes


cardList[].description
StringObject array
The object array containing the description of the content
No


cardList[].imageUrl
URLObject
The object containing the URL of the image to display
No


cardList[].linkUrl
URLObject
The object containing the URL of the content
No


cardList[].press
StringObject
The object containing the name of the press
No


cardList[].pressIconUrl
URLObject
The object containing the URL of the press icon
No


cardList[].publishDate
DateObject
The object containing the publishing date of the article
No


cardList[].referenceText
StringObject
The object containing the text information of the source
No


cardList[].referenceURL
URLObject
The object containing the URL of the source
No


cardList[].title
StringObject
The object containing the title of the content
No


cardList[].videoUrl
URLObject
The object containing the URL of the video to play
No


subType
string
Card type identifier. You may specify four types as follows. Type1Type2Type3Type4Note!Type1, Type2, Type3 are represented as an empty string at the moment. You need to determine which type to use based on the available fields of each card object.
Yes


type
string
Content Template identifier. Fixed to "CardList".
Yes



Template Example
// Type1, Type2 example:
// User request: 공포 영화 추천해줘 (Request to recommend a horror movie).

{
  "subType": "",
  "type": "CardList",
  "cardList": [
    {
      "description": [
        {
          "type": "string",
          "value": "공포, 스릴러"
        },
        {
          "type": "string",
